a. Java 21.0.2
b. Java SE (Standard edition)
       = Used for desktop applications
       = "General purpose" version that is not specialised for any particular use as opposed to other versions of Java that contain special classes and other features
             
   Java ME (Micro Edition)
       = Used for mobile device and embedded system applications
       = Comes with additional class libraries useful for small devices
      
c. Windows. Linux, and MacOS

d. IntelliJ IDEA

e. The main function indicates the starting point for the java program to execute. Without it, the code wouldn't be able to run as it wouldn't know when to start.